## Summary of US-005

**Diff (Excel `Provider_Developer_Analysis` rows 1-19 vs v28)**: all analysis text already matched Excel, but seven cell popups were misaligned:
1. Scope EU — wrong verbatim (Art 3(3) instead of Art 50)
2. Reg trigger TX — empty popup
3. Transparency EU — empty popup
4. Transparency CO — empty popup
5. General info disclosure TX — empty popup
6. Risk management TX — empty popup
7. AI literacy EU — empty popup

**Fix**: Added `apply_limited_risk_provider_fixes` to `build_v28.py` — slices the limited-risk Provider sub-concept JSON segment and applies seven scoped string-level cell-triple swaps (necessary because the limited-risk Deployer table has identical empty-cell triples that would collide with global replacements). EU verbatim sourced from `law-blob-eu-ai-act`; Texas verbatim from `law-blob-tx-hb149`; Colorado reference label set without verbatim (CO law-blob has no embedded sections).

**Verified**: 8/8 tests pass (`test_lexicon_v28.py` T8 added) and each of the seven fixed cells confirmed via `gstack /browse` to display the corrected `drawer-ref` and verbatim opening line.

